<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> Axelrod, Deborah, MD, et al. <a href="http://www.ijoeh.com/pfds/1003_Axelrod.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ijoeh.com/pfds/1003_Axelrod.pdf" rel="nofollow">"'Hormesis'—An Inappropriate Extrapolation from the Specific to the Universal"</a>. International Journal of Occupational and Environmental Health, 2004;10:335–339. Retrieved 26-Feb-2006.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<p>NOTE: An early version of this article was based on the press handout: "Hormesis: Principal Concepts and Take Home Message", by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Edward_J._Calabrese&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Edward J. Calabrese (page does not exist)">Edward J. Calabrese</a>, Ph.D., University of Massachusetts, from a hormesis panel discussion, Feb 25, 2004, Washington, DC.</p>
